    "about": "Researcher @ Thinking Machines Lab, building things one auto-accept-edit-on at a time .\n\nPast:\n- Mistral: laid the foundation of full audio stack, core contributor to data pipeline, tokenizer, pretraining, post-training, and audio-out inference. also worked on small LLMs. all results open-sourced with report.\n- Nvidia: research intern, multiple publications in audio foundation models.\n- FAIR: research intern, published in (1) unsupervised learning methods for speech; (2) pretraining framework for audio generation. The technique was later productized for Meta's multimodal generative models.\n- MIT: doctoral research in speech representation learning and generative models.\n\nSee personal webpage for more info: https://alexander-h-liu.github.io/",
